criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with chronic non-specific low back pain, with symptoms present for at least
             three months;

          -  Patients with a pain intensity of at least 50mm (measured by a 0-100 mm Visual Analog
             Scale);

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Serious spinal pathologies (such as fractures, tumors, inflammatory, and infectious
             diseases);

          -  Patients who used local corticosteroids and/or botulin toxin injection for pain relief
             within the prior 30 days of the beginning of the study;

          -  Chronic pain diseases as fibromyalgia and diabetic type 1;

          -  Neuropathic pain;

          -  Previous spinal surgery in the past 12 months;

          -  Cancer patients;

          -  Pregnancy or breast feeding.
